<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Dev Tunnels on MCP Explorer</title><link>https://mcp-explorer-x-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/dev-tunnels/</link><description>Recent content in Dev Tunnels on MCP Explorer</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-explorer-x-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/dev-tunnels/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Using Dev Tunnels</title><link>https://mcp-explorer-x-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/dev-tunnels/using-dev-tunnels/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-explorer-x-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/dev-tunnels/using-dev-tunnels/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview"&gt;Overview &lt;a href="#overview" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Dev Tunnels&lt;/strong&gt; page — labelled &lt;em&gt;Signal Deck&lt;/em&gt; in the UI — is MCP Explorer&amp;rsquo;s built-in webhook ingress control room. It wraps Microsoft&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/developer/dev-tunnels/get-started" rel="external" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;code&gt;devtunnel&lt;/code&gt; CLI&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to create a stable public HTTPS callback URL, captures every HTTP request that arrives at that URL in real time via SSE, and lets you inspect or replay those requests without leaving the app.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>